Msg.ExtDesc:
When installing SPB tools that interface with OpenAccess, it is necessary for OpenAccess to be configured after installation of the core tools. You may verify that OpenAccess has been properly installed for your software by looking for a folder beginning with "oa_v22" in the SPB install hierarchy root directory.
On Linux and UNIX systems, there should be a share/oa soft link which points to the above OpenAccess installation directory. Finally, there should be a share/oaPlugIns directory which contains the cdsLib.plg file.
On Windows systems, the OA_PLUGIN_PATH environment variable must be set to point to the share/oaPlugIns directory.
If any of the above is not properly configured, run the installation and/or configuration tools again. Once finished, you will need to restart this program for the changes to take effect.
